The paper focuses on the analysis of channel state information (CSI) in multi-antenna downlink networks for physical layer security. This topic falls under the sub-category of information theory (cs.IT) as it deals with the transmission and processing of information over communication channels. Additionally, the paper also involves network infrastructure (cs.NI) as it discusses multi-user networks. The concept of physical layer security also falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The use of multiple antennas in the network also relates to the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM) as it involves the transmission of multiple streams of data. Finally, the paper also involves the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SI) as it deals with the processing of the channel state information.
